						<summary>

						<p>In the same place.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Paridhāvi, Aṟpaśi 10 = 1492 A.D., October 9.</hi> </p>						

						<p>This inscription is damaged at the end.</p>						

						<p>It records the endowment of a dancing girl named Araṅguḷattāḷ, renamed as Tiruchchirāppaḷḷimāṇikkam to the temple of Tirumuttīśuram-uḍaiya-nāyaṉār, by the residents of Kīḻaik-Kaḍuvaṉkuḍi. Koḍumbāḷūr is mentioned at the end.</p>						

						</summary>
